<%@ Page Language="C#" MasterPageFile="~/MainMasterPage.master" AutoEventWireup="true" CodeFile="Default.aspx.cs" Inherits="_Default" Title="Untitled Page" %>
<asp:Content ID="Content1" ContentPlaceHolderID="ContentPlaceHolder1" Runat="Server">
    <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="publicloginTable" height="400"
        width="100%">
        <tr>
            <td align="center" style="width: 96%" valign="top">
            <div style="text-align:left">
            
                <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 9pt; text-indent: 0.5in; text-align: justify">
                    <span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">This
                        project is aimed at developing a web based Leave Management Tool, which is of importance
                        to either an organization or a college.
                        <?xml namespace="" ns="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" prefix="o" ?><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in; text-align: justify">
                    <span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                        <o:p>&nbsp;</o:p>
                    </span>
                </p>
                <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 9pt; text-indent: 0.5in; text-align: justify">
                    <span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">The
                        <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Easy Leave </b> is an Intranet based application
                        that can be accessed throughout the organization or a specified group/Dept. This
                        system can be used to automate the workflow of leave applications and their approvals.
                        The periodic crediting of leave is also automated. There are features like email
                        notifications, cancellation of leave, automatic approval of leave, report generators
                        etc in this Tool.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in; text-align: justify">
                    <span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'"><span
                        style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt 9pt; text-indent: 0.5in; text-align: justify">
                    <span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">There
                        are registered people in the system. Some are approvers. An approver can also be
                        a requestor. In an organization, the hierarchy could be Engineers/Managers/Business
                        Managers/Managing Director etc. In a college, it could be Lecturer/Professor/Head
                        of the Department/Dean/Principal etc.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify">
                    <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black;
                        font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                        <o:p>&nbsp;</o:p>
                    </span></b>
                </p>
                <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 9pt; text-align: justify">
                    <span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">Following
                        is a list of functionalities of the system:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <ol start="1" style="margin-top: 0in" type="1">
                    <li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                        mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                            A person should be able to
                            <o:p></o:p>
                        </span></li>
                    <ul style="margin-top: 0in" type="disc">
                        <li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                            mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                                login to the system through the first page of the application
                                <o:p></o:p>
                            </span></li>
                        <li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                            mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                                change the password after logging into the system<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                            mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                                see his/her eligibility details (like how many days of leave he/she is eligible
                                for etc)<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                            mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                                query the leave balance<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                            mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                                see his/her leave history since the time he/she joined the company/college<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                            mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                                apply for leave, specifying the from and to dates, reason for taking leave, address
                                for communication while on leave and his/her superior’s email id<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                            mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                                see his/her current leave applications and the leave applications that are submitted
                                to him/her for approval or cancellation
                                <o:p></o:p>
                            </span></li>
                        <li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                            mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                                approve/reject the leave applications that are submitted to him/her<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                            mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                                withdraw his/her leave application (which has not been approved yet)<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                            mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                                Cancel his/her leave (which has been already approved). This will need to be approved
                                by his/her Superior<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                            mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                                get help about the leave system on how to use the different features of the system<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul>
                    <li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                        mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                            As soon as a leave application /cancellation request /withdrawal /approval /rejection
                            /password-change is made by the person, an automatic email should be sent to the
                            person and his superior giving details about the action<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                        mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                            The number of days of leave (as per the assumed leave policy) should be automatically
                            credited to everybody and a notification regarding the same be sent to them automatically<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                        mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                            An automatic leave-approval facility for leave applications which are older than
                            2 weeks should be there. Notification about the automatic leave approval should
                            be sent to the person as well as his superior<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                        mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                            A summary report of the leave details of his/her sub-ordinates should be sent to
                            every manager periodically<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; color: black; text-align: justify;
                        mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Verdana','sans-serif'">
                            A calendar giving the public holidays of the organization/college should be available
                            on the system<o:p></o:p></span></li></ol>
            </div>
            </td>
        </tr>
